To grab a frame from the video:

dir=2016-05; time=67; ffmpeg -ss $time -i ~/Desktop/scienceknocks/episodes/$dir/$dir.mp4 -vframes 1 -f image2 ~/Desktop/scienceknocks/episodes/$dir/$dir.jpg


To get the time, in seconds, for a file

dir=2016-05; for media in mp3 mp4; do ffprobe -i ~/Desktop/scienceknocks/episodes/$dir/$dir.$media -show_entries format=duration -v quiet -of csv="p=0"; done;


